title: Maritime Security Officer
name: Robert Noe
description: Provide security as a member of maritime quick reaction force team tasked with the at sea and in port protection of the Sea Based X-Band radar (SBX-1), a $1.5 Billion dollar Missile Defense Agency SSL-A asset that is a component of the ground-based midcourse defense element of the Ballistic Missile Defense System. Maintain a current Secret clearance, Level I Antiterrorism Certification, and small/heavy arms certification on the M2HB machine gun, M240 machine gun, Beretta 9mm handgun, M-4 rifle and M500 Shotgun. Primary duties include monitoring of the Integrated Electronic Security System/CCure, access control, roving security patrols, cargo freight inspections, and response to terrorism, sabotage and theft. Trained in the use of the Long Range Acoustic Device, Retractable Baton, weapons retention/disarming, handcuffing and surveillance/counter-surveillance.
